The paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to generate distractors for multiple choice reading comprehension questions. This falls under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed hierarchical encoder-decoder framework with attention mechanisms also involves techniques related to deep learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques to identify relevant sentences from the reading comprehension article (cs.IR).
